OL,3,CPetition calls to cancel costly by-
OL,4,Celection for disgraced ex-politician
OL,6,F"I do think that to go out and vote
OL,7,Ffor just one seat, one person. I think
OL,8,Fpeople will stay away and say,
OL,9,Fwhatever happens, happens."
OL,11,FGuernsey politician Deputy Marc Laine
OL,12,Fsupports the cancellation of the by-
OL,13,Felection, stating that he will
OL,14,Finitiate a requete - a formal
OL,15,Fpolitical petition - to stop it from
OL,16,Fhappening.
OL,18,FDeputy Laine claims nearly half the
OL,19,FDeputies support it, but it is
OL,20,Funderstood the requete will not be
OL,21,Fvoted on until next year.
